\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well, good citizen and respectable. No swearing, very strong point, no lies - wouldn't tell lies. I think she'd sooner you swear than tell lies, and I've stuck to it, and I think 
it's very good for anybody. I'd sooner hear my children swear than telling lies I know that, don't know how to cope with lies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 She obviously thought honesty very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Anything else outstanding you think she'd emphasise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No,
 don't think so, no, she was not a religious woman, she didn't like church. And I never heard her swear and she was good to everybody. Actually really I think a lot of them people more than I do some of the church people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well we'd probably get a few coppers you know, penny here or penny there. Perhaps a - little luxury for tea you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have any guests in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Perhaps one or two friends. Very small, nothing elaborate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you used to get presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, just a few coppers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember anything you did with your mother on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well we used to hang our stockings up and - get a few nuts and - gold pennies at that time. A little C
hristmas stocking, you know, ordinary small stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 The chocolate gold pennies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes. That's right, yes. No, the real gold pennies. The real gold pennies them days. Yes. No, what we called gold, new pennies. Yes. Yes, they was like - gold to us. W
e always got them. A few nuts and that and - take the bed down in the kitchen and - we'd have a little do you know, a - little extra, perhaps celery for tea. Home made cake. Stop up late and - stop up 'til perhaps nine or ten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you get a big present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember any big presents. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Not when I was younger, when we got older we had a piano. When I was younger there was no - musical -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 After you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh yes
. Yes. I understand we had a piano - when me father died and mother couldn't keep the - payments up so they took it away. Yes. Yes. 'Cos she couldn't get no money then. Not a ha'penny off of anybody. You either had to go and have free }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 meals}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  or go up to the work house and get some - free food you know. There was no money allowed at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Not a great lot, no, we wasn't a - musical family, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother play any games with you in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, just the ordinary ones, ludo and snakes and ladders. As we got older, cards you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, we had quite a - few books. In fact I've still got 'em, we had - set of Dickens' and set of - Scotts' books. Ra
ther old stage stuff to me, you know what I mean, but - evidently they was - all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 rage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  them days, you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know who bought these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I should think by the - the look of 'em, the date of 'em they've been handed down, you know, from a
nother family. Probably father's people or mother's people which I wouldn't know about. Very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember reading any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I read some of Dickens' yes. I couldn't get on with Scotts'. Too dry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, we had a - newspaper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember which one it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 We used to have Reynolds of a Sunday. The daily paper - I've got an idea it was the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426  Mirror}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  or the Sketch. I wouldn't be certain about it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't remember seeing them. One or two comics perhaps but - give us kids you know but - no regular - delivery of magazines, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother do much reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, she didn't have a lot of time really, all I can remember her doing nearly every nig
ht was washing and ironing and - keeping the house tidy, she was a very clean person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did she ever read out loud to you when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 1918. No, I doubt it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Very seldom. No. I can't - lack - lack of funds again I expect. And clothes - you didn't have the clothes to go out in really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 It must have limited things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Scope of going out - social life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you used to go out shopping with your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about Bank Holidays or days out, did you get any of these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well, Bank Holidays, mostly as I - can remember we u
sed to go out with what we called the School Union, we - I think we used to pay about a penny. And they took us out for a day to Loughton or somewhere like that. Bank Holidays. But I can't remember the family going out, the school would arrange. School pa
rty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Day school, not Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, school parties, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Could you tell us how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well - Saturday mornings - I definitely used to go and clean me a
unt's silver as I said - knives and forks. And - probably take me up to about twelve o'clock. Afternoons, probably me eldest brother used to take me to - football. Saturday evenings perhaps a game indoors, cards or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What was football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Professional team you know. Leyton Orient, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Sunday. Sunday morning get up, breakfast and - probably put on our best clothes if we had any at the time - have our dinner. That's about all. Sunday afternoon we proba
bly played games or go out over the park, we was - very near Victoria Park was round the corner to us, we spent a lot of time there. I used to go to Sunday school up to when I was about thirteen. Mother was not religious as I said but - she made us go 'ti
l we was old enough to know our own mind. And - I went quite up - fourteen or fifteen I think. Used to go to Sunday school Sunday afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 She considered you knew your own mind when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, that's right, round about fourteen, fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have different clothes for Sunday, did you have best clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Probably you would have a new pair of trousers, and you've had them - perhaps two or three weeks and then you'd have to take 'em for school. Back to the old routine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Your mother didn't mind you playing or working on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother ever go to a place of worship at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know what denomination she would have called herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Atheist she was. She was an atheist, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know why she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, I don't know whether she had the same - reason as me, as - as I got it that we met a lot worse church people than ourself. In fact we had one or two neighbours that - went to church and the vicar used to come
 round and they was really blackguards but - which really turned me and in my young days against religion more than anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You were conscious of this while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Teenager I should say, yes, fourteen, fifteen. These women used
 to row and fight and swear each other, and then they'd go church on a Sunday. And there was me mother never went to church, never swore, never got into trouble. And I think really that - changed me more than anything, or made my mind up shall I say. I wa
s
 actually a choirboy at one time you know when I was young. More so I think because we used to get about a shilling a quarter for being in it you know. But of course when I - We used to go to Sunday school and that sort of thing to - for a change, kind of
 a different atmosphere and a little more entertainment I suppose you'd call it. Just a break form the - small house we was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I suppose it was one of the few chances you'd get to hear a bit of music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes, yes, or - like meet somebody different you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Because you didn't have radios or anything then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, no, you had to - make all your own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you get on for music then, you hear it everywhere you go now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well of course you hadn't been brought up to it so you didn't miss it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were barrel organs and things like that very common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, barrel organs was, yes. Salvation Army bands on a Sunday morning, used to come and play and you'd all turn out and listen to that or open your windows - hear it, but - and barrel organs, they were very frequent, up and down the street. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And people would really go out and give them a penny or something?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh yes, yes, yes. And then Saturday evenings you'd see 'em dancing round it, yes - yes, it was part of the entertainment. Yes.a
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And people used to make a point of listening to anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You went to Sunday school, what sort of Sunday school was it, was it chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, Church of England. Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes. Yes. Very local - well, I say local, it was a long way for us then but it was only - Epping Forest or Loughton. Which would what be fourteen, fifteen mile I suppose. Not as far as the seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You never went to the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, no. Can't remember - 'til I got married, or - courting perhaps. Remember - never remember going to sea when I was - at school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you used to get to Epping Forest or Loughton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 In brakes at that time. Horse brakes. Yes, four-horse brakes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of things would they organise for you on these outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh races you know, you'd have a - big meat pie for dinner, I remember that vividly. It was real - really a good meal, and you'd have a 
bag of sweets, orange, apple and you'd have races in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 More like a children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 s sports day sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you ever attend the church or just the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any other social activities organised by the church, any that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Not when I was at school. When I left school I joined the mission club - the Manor club it's called then, they was very good to us. We was all poor boys and of course it'
s a well known club. And we - you join that - you can't join that 'til you're fourteen. That was round the corner to us so - the influence but - as I say, Sunday school, you'd probably have a Christmas treat, and this annual - holiday to Loughton or somew
here like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What was at Loughton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well it was only fields, and - a few swings. Donkey rides. 'Course I believe now it's a town you know, but in them days it was country to us, you know. No seaside but - you'd have donkey rides and swings, se
esaws and - big day for us London kids naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You say you belonged to the choir, did they have a special outing, did you get anything extra for being in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, you only used to get - I don't know what it was - shilling or something a quarter, for belonging to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did the church run a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 temperance club}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well - I wouldn't - I don't know - by a temperance club but when we was young we had a Band of Hope, we used to go to a Band of Hope meeting Tuesday night, that was to bring you up against drink and that. Yes. Yes, a junior - temperance affair, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of activities did they have, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Tuesday night, well you start off with the hymns you know. And then perhaps the parson'd give you a talk and then y
ou'll have games up and down the hall. And on ropes, things like that. Couple of hours. I think we used to have to take a farthing or ha'penny, put it in the basin. Then also they had a outing once a year you know somewhere. Yes, rather that off on the br
akes. Yes. Yes. I suppose really that's why we went, just for these outings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any other clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, at that time the Manor was the club for - between fourteen and eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Or say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know whether your mother took any interest in politics at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, very little. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know whether she voted before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I should say she did, yes, I should think - and I think them days she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 . Yes, almost sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did she take part in any canvassing or did she belong to the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 She'd just go and vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Vote. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When your mother wasn't working how would she spend her spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Working. You know, practically always doing something in the house, you know, scrubbing or - spring cleaning or - mending, darning, suchlike. No, nothing else. She never used to go to mothers meetings or - outings or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 She didn't have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 She didn't go out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, her enjoyment was in her home if you can call it enjoyment, I suppose at was to her. Bringing up her family and that. We'd probably go
 and get her - or the eldest brother'd get her half a pint of stout now and again. I never known her to go in pubs, not when she was a widow. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know whether she belonged }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  any savings clubs, funeral clubs or boot clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, I think we used to pay a - tally - you know, we used to call 'em tallymen at the time - about a bob a week, and probably we have a new pair of shoes or something like that, yes. Not on a big scale you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did they have any relatives or friends or neighbours living nearby?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, had neighbours and friends but - never mixed that much you know like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did you manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well the eldest sister either looked after or stop at home. And often ten days they got up when they was ill. But if it was too bad naturally the eldest sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You wouldn't get any help from the neighbours or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
I suppose you would if you wanted it but we - mother was rather close that way, she never encouraged - a lot people come in your house and she didn't go in there. We was friendly with neighbours but - we didn't have 'em in the house, that - yes, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Why was this, was this because the neighbours were a bit rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well it - it was a rough neighbourhood but - I don't think it was pride. It was just because she didn't want to get mixed with 'em, she was one of them person that thought that if 
you didn't get mixed with 'em you didn't get into trouble. Fact she was really known as the peacemaker down there, you know, if there was any squabbles and that she used to try and - smooth it over if anything. Yes. Wasn't at all quarrelsome. Yes. That's 
right, and of course them days I mean - most of the poor people, they was always inclined to be short tempered and squabbling you know how I mean. Things wasn't as comfortable as they might have been, not for anybody you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you think this made a difference to the atmosphere of people, made them more quarrelsome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh I'm sure it did. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 
I mean - probably - about Wednesday you'd have perhaps two or three shillings to get to the end of the week with, and you were worrying to how to get the next dinner and that so - the least little thing would - upset you, you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And you saw quite a lot of neighbours quarrelling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. I - I should say more so than today. I think more today they quarrel over - 'cos they've got more than one another. The
m days it was 'cos they had less than one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you see much of your relatives that lived nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, we didn't see 'em a lot. No, didn't. Weren't a lot of entertaining them days. No. I suppose we - we had really a closer life 'cos the mother left with the children and going to work you see. When she come homes was working again, you know, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 staying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
 in and all of us up. Ironing and - washing and that. Yes. She had to go to work to pay the rent, you couldn't - I think she only getting about e
ighteen bob a week. When she first started. Well of course - soon after me eldest brother started and he fetched in a few bob so - we got on a bit. You had to be pretty hard up to get any free meals, what I had to go to. You couldn't get them easy. Man wo
uld come down and look at your place and - take all particulars down. You had to be really hard up to get them free meals.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Can you remember this chap coming round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I wouldn't say I could. I knew they come. Relieving officers they were called. Them days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother ever invite friends into the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Not to my memory, no, I can't remember. I don't think we had hardly anybody in the houses 'til the older ones started courting. Yes. We had a big night then. Clean cloth on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You mean matter of class? No, I should say - 'cos I was - I was
n't all that old then, fifteen and under, and to me, I only knew one class really was the poor class you know, I didn't - I didn't know much about the - middle classes and the - the practically all poor class that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You weren't really conscious of the class thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, no, I wasn't really old enough to - understand the class business. I knew there were classes, but - practically all my young days was the poor class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What class would you call yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Poor class. I don't mean bad class, poor - poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Who would you say were the most important people in your neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well - that's a bit difficult isn't it. 'Course - once I joined the - the Manor club, the - the gentleman that run that club was important to me. But otherwise
 the important people was me mother and - I would have - brothers and sisters you know. We didn't mix a lot, I didn't know a lot of people, but of course once I joined the club, I got mixed, you know, used to think a lot of them gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of chaps were they that ran this club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh they was from Eton, that's why it was called Eton Manor. There was a - a Mr Wellesley, he only died a couple of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 years ago}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 , he was a grandson of the Duke of Wellington, people like that, Mr Wagg and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were they ex-students?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well, they was well-to-do sons and - they was all bachelors and they used to live near there in a big house in Hackney Wick at the back of this Eton Manor Club, they was all young men at the time. There was about half a dozen of t
hem. They all had money, and of course, there was what they called a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 trust}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
 from the Eton College, used to keep the - club running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What class would you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Top class I should think. Yes, definitely. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 As myself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Where would you draw the line sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well them days to me I think - you'd say poor class and then we used to look upon our teachers as different class, they used to live - a few min
utes walk away and they'd have bigger houses, one or two or 'em had a servant, you know. Doctors. That kind of people I'd say was a - a class upwards you know. I think nowadays teachers are almost - I'm ordinary that we're all better class. But them days 
to me teachers, as I say, teachers, doctors, such people was - better class to me, they lived in better houses, had more rooms, better clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 The difference in the clothes was more noticeable in those days was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Nowadays you look at people today and it's difficult to tell what class they are?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
That's right, yes. Then you knew I mean - I mean you'd see - see the same people always down - round the rag stall on a Sunday morning. That was the poor class you know. 
And as I say practically all them teachers and that, they'd either have a servant or they'd have different clothes weekends you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about white collar workers, where would you have put those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 They're - some was middle class, some were stil
l poor class. I had a brother and sister, brother especially, he was a white collar and - he - he lived with us and what we say the poor class and I've seen him have little paper collars on and - at one time he wore spats, he - he'd cut boots down, make a
 
pair of shoes of 'em just to keep up appearance. He was a clerk in the city you know. And - he tried to be different to us in his way but - of course he still had to come down to our level regards his food and one thing and another. He's a nice enough cha
p, but - he was a white collar worker. And I suppose - he didn't ought to have been really, he couldn't keep up to it you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No I wouldn't say so because - we practically met the same sort all the time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 'Til we joined the club and then - then - better class people you naturally respected because they was working for you, you know, was helping you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
And it's all according to your bringing up ain't it, I mean I was brought up to respect people and it sort automatically come to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you taught to touch your cap or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. Never touched me cap but - always respectable, good morning or goodnight or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you taught to call anyone sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Only in school, naturally. But of course in the ordinary you didn't often meet many sirs or madams where we lived you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Who do you think the shopkeepers associated with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I'd say middle class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about the clergyman, what did you think of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
I should say they was middle class although I suppose - I've learned since they wasn't really because they was no better paid than - many of the others, but to us in them days - I should 
say they was middle class. Yes, they had a - regular food and - and bigger house than us sort of thing which - made you think they was - better class and probably they was - almost as hard up as we was. As you grow old and read the - you know, what their 
living was and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about employers, did you know any employers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I - I worked when I was a schoolboy - of a morning on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 milk round}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  you know and - I should say in them days employers was hard up. They treated you harder, you had t
o do your work better or - or else you'd soon be out - on your neck which is all - different nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Would you say there was any difference between church and chapel people, did you know any chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, only since I've got old I've know the - yes, not when I was young I didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When you were young what sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well - on the one had I should say - what I consider mumpers and cadgers that used to go for what they could get, and then you'd ge
t the middle class - shopkeepers, schoolteachers who went because they wanted to do. But I think half the working class who went to church only went to get what they could out of it. Yes. Yes. Or go and have tea and cake with the Vicar one day, that sort 
of thing you see. Mother never believed in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I should say - some lived a better - fo
r instance, like our family - some of the families had a husband at work although - I wouldn't say they lived tip-top, they lived better than we did you know, I mean their children didn't have to go out for free meals such as I did and things like that yo
u know. And they'd probably have a - a little better clothes at weekend and that you know. And probably Saturday or Sunday night the parents'd go out and have a drink, which wasn't - in our - life you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Oh definitely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You were conscious of this division as a child were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of things would put people in one group rather than another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well you know people like ourselves
 - you know, at home respectable, and then you'd have a - people regular Saturday nights go out and have a beer and - fight you know. Yes, that was the main two classes in the - in the poor district. What we used to call the boozers. And they'd do it regu
l
ar, I mean that was their life, even lived - lived right next door to us. Best people out all the week but this Saturday night they'd have their fling, booze up. Yes, regular. Pawn shop - go to pawn shop Mondays. Whereas - well not because we didn't have 
m
uch to pawn but we very seldom went to pawn. If you didn't have it you just went without but of course the booze - what we called the boozing families mostly used the pawn shop. Queues of a Monday morning at the pawn shop. And mostly the regular people, a
nd the regular stuff they take, the old man's suit and shoes, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And your mother used to avoid this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. As much as possible. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 Very, very rare. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 As I say, we didn't have a lot to pawn but we didn't - 'cos she says you only have t
o pay extra on it at the end of the week and get it out. I've heard neighbours say they - you know, when winters come on, right worried 'cos they've got to get the old man's overcoat out of pawn, you know. He don't know it's in pawn. They're a bit despera
te when the weather starts getting cold and they say, where's me bloody overcoat? Often heard that you know. Real, I mean, this is - actually what happened.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember any distinction like this between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I wouldn't say so, I don't - didn't - remember a lot about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother have the same attitude to people in different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, I think so, as far as she didn't meet a lot of different class people. But she was a very level minded wom
an, you know what I mean. She was never envious of anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you think she saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so. She was a - just an ordinary hard working woman, that's - as far as she knew and as far as she went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You don't think it would have entered her mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I should say no, it was very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You don't remember anyone doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you 
remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady? Was this an expression you ever heard used? What would you think of as a real gent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I wouldn't say so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you see much of the police round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Police? Oh yes. Yes, very active Saturday nights - round the pubs, also we had the River Lee right near us and - very often got bodies out of there, bring them along on hand stretchers, we used to follow 'em - to the police station. They used - used t
o mostly go about in pairs in them days. All foot policemen naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Why was this, were they liable to get beaten up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh yes. Saturday nights. Fighting three or four men, one copper couldn't - deal with them on his own you know. Regular Satur
day, I mean, that's part of our enjoyment, our pub people. Used to hear the whistles going and the coppers running. And then - as I say, as a kid we used to follow this - ambulance with the body on it. Take it to the mortuary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was it quite common for people to drown themselves or fall in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well the River Lee, I reckon on you could reckon on one week. If not two, yes, I don't know whether they fell in or took their own life. Children used to swim in it and get in trouble. Yes. Yes, of course not so
 many baths, swimming baths and that, they - I mean, when we was kids we used to say, come on, have a swim in the cut, which we used to call the River Lee. You'd have dozens of kids swimming you know. Often one get caught in the weeds or something like th
at. Nobody looking after 'em. I mean nine times out of ten probably the mother didn't know they'd gone
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You don't see much of scrapping in the streets after the pubs close now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No, no. You'd practically find it was the same families every week
 - kind of a feud you know, a couple next door would have a - dust up with a couple turnings away and that - that with the same people you know, and - I - I think it's part of their fun. It's part of their weekend, you know, if they hadn't had a fight - y
ou know, if they hadn't had a fight they hadn't had a good weekend. There's no doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How do you think the police treated people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well I don't see 'em - as far as I remember - ill treat 'em you know, they used to - I mean
 in fact sometimes they'd just - give you a clip round the ear and take you home if you're drunk, but of course if you got a bit funny and that they used to - we used to go along jeering 'em and - hooting 'em and that you know, but I think they only used 
t
o get fined about five shillings or bound over, or probably keep 'em in for a couple of hours and then send 'em home you know if they wasn't fighting, if they was just drunk you know. I think you see more drunks laying about then than these days you know.
 Yes. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When you were naughty did your mother ever scare you, telling you she would call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember that threat. It was often used in our - working class people but I can't say as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you frightened of the police as a child or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Your home was rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you see anything of the landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well the landlord's agent used to come every Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What did you feel about them as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well - fair, I - I always got the impression that he thought he was much better class than us. You know, he had a better suit - trilby hat and - he used to try and - I'd say almost bully you sometimes you know, if - perhaps if you di
dn't have the money or you wanted some decorating you know. Very officious sort of person. Always think he thought he was a - above us you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What were they like about doing repairs and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Pretty hard, yes. And you didn't do 
'em yourself, you couldn't afford it. You didn't know how to really, nobody I knew - perhaps a little bit of whitewashing but as for - paper and that you didn't know. No, the houses used to be pretty rough by the time they did do anything. Main thing was 
- rain coming in you know. They'd ignore it, you'd have buckets perhaps, on the floor or bowls. Shift the bed over so it wouldn't get wet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 They were as bad as that were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes, oh yes. You were very lucky if you had a house that didn't - the rain didn't come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember as a child feeling that your mother had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh yes. Definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What did you think about this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well - I suppose when you're that age you accept it. It
's part of your life and you put up with it, it's later on you think - what your mother went through. When you're too late, when you - when it's finished, there's no doubt about that, I mean, then as I say you used to go to school, go out to play, mother 
still working or washing or trying to get next day's dinner. But it's when you get off it's that you think back what a life they had. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You got help with these free meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you get any help from the Guardians of the Parish or any other charities that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
I think mother used to go up on a Friday, we used to call to see the relieving officer and she would bring home a couple of loaves, sugar - rice, one or two odds and ends but - never cash. Never money. Bread, perha
ps they'd give you too much bread, but - ordinary - before you got that the man would come down have a look at your home to see that - you didn't have anything worth selling and that, that was very strict and hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How do you think the relieving officers treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well we had a fairly decent one but - it was common that some of them were - very tight, but we had quite a decent fellow as I remember him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So you were fairly fortunate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. I think so, yes. He could only give us wh
at he had, you know what I mean, he - he couldn't give us any extra 'cos he was a good fellow but - he talked to you better when he come to see you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 He could be pleasant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, that's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you feel about getting the charity then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well when I was young it was part of me life, you know what I mean. I didn't have to go once - when I was older and married and the only time in me life that I was really ashamed of myself. But when I was young, didn't matter you know. No do
ubt mother felt it, as I say, we didn't know her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 feelings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  then. We was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you feel set apart from the other kids or anything like this at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 All right, yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you feel close to any particular one of them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so, pretty general.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Who did you play with as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Boys mostly, yes, about my own age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, well you see m
e two brothers was older. Me two sisters was next to me. Which therefore is that gap which - really I went out with boys you know in the street, mates and that you see. Me brothers was what - twelve, fourteen years older than me. Made that gap you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Where did you play as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Mostly in the street - as I say we had the park right near us. Used to go over there a lot, that was just round the corner to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of games did you play then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well, football, cricket. Just ordinary boy recreation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, were not - no restriction. Apart being careful of me clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, as far as I remember, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Your mother didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No. No. No restriction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you belong to any youth organisations before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies, did you collect stamps or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, probably cigarette cards, used to play a lot of marbles and - them sort of boys games and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about tops or hoops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Tops was in vogue, yes, spinning tops. Hoops for the girls. Peg tops as we called 'em. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Hoops were more for girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you keep any pets or do any gardening or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was there anywhere where you could go fishing, you say you'd go swimming in the River Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 The cut - the Riv
er Lee. No, I can't recollect that. We'd probably do a little bit of fishing with a ordinary net you know but - nothing like the boys do nowadays. NO. I mean you didn't go anywhere, you didn't have the money for the fares and that, it was only - local pon
ds. Used to take a net perhaps, little jar for tiddlers. Yes. Yes, yes. Tadpoles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you ever bike when you were a kid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Not when I was a kid, no. More in me teens. The first bike I had I remember - paid half a crown deposit on it, buying it week
ly. I was in me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426  teens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
 - I was in work then. Earning me own money. We used to have a bike out on hire, tuppence an hour you could get. A local shop or shed, yes, we used to - if you had tuppence you could have this - old bike for an hour, you know, ride about on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, football, cricket mostly - at school and then on to the club afterwards, very keen on football and cricket, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were these organised teams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. School teams, schoolboy teams. Used to play on a dinner time or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about theatres, concerts, music halls when you were a kid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 No, very, very few, it wasn't - can't recollect them much.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Cinemas we used to go Saturday morning for a treat, we used 
to pay a penny. We used to call it the flea pit. You'd pay a penny and you'd go in and - you'd get a comic, woman on the piano you know, playing down the front. But we didn't always do that but - there was a Saturday matinee mornings. With a penny, get a 
comic, yes. Comic or a stick of rock sometimes. A little treat. Same as you have a haircut, about three ha'pence for a haircut, you always got a toy - toy with it, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any other things, there's nothing like this nowadays is there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No
, no, no, could - you'd probably go - three months 'fore you hand a haircut. It was a desperate pull out for the parents and - you know, they earned their money and then you had to have it right close to your head. All right for that you always got a toy 
or a comic or something, to entice you I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any other people apart from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 cinemas }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 and the barbers who'd give inducements like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh you - if you was a good customer at the bakers - you used to get a stale cake and you'd prob
ably go half a mile to get a couple of loaves, to this shop who give you the stale cakes, if they'd had some over from the day before. Because - kids of that age, stale cake was quite a treat. I recollect that quite easy. And we'd go to a market, I daresa
y it was what - half a mile, perhaps threequarters of a mile away, to get marg a ha'penny cheaper. Anything like that, that was - dinnertime task }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 for mum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 , to go and get - pound of marg or half of marg a ha'penny cheaper you know. Had - just had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Would you go all this way to get a ha'penny pocket money for yourself or was this to save your mum money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Save your mum money, used to get ha'penny on Friday, I can remember that. More often than not we used to buy a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 ha'porth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  of broken biscuits, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You didn't buy many sweets with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, you was glad to buy biscuits, that was a - treat. Or - or perhaps - fried potatoes at the fish shop, used to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 ha'penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  bit and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 ha'porth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  we used to call it in then days. That was a odd bit of fish and a few chips you know. You could get that. Well we often had that for dinner anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 This was your only regular pocket money was it on Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, ha'penny, yes. Perhaps you'd run a - errand for your neighbour, get another ha'p
enny during the week or something like that. Yes, yes, you - you'd run a couple of errands, and as I said I used to get this tuppence off me aunt for doing the odd chores you know. And of course that'd go a long way then, penny for the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you do anything else for this aunt for the tuppence or was it just Saturday morning cleaning the knives and forks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, that's all I had to do for the - and then as I got older of course I went on a milk job early in the morning you know. I - I suppose
 I was about twelve then. I forget what I got, couple of bob I suppose, eighteen pence something like that, which mum used to have and she'd perhaps give me a couple of coppers back. And then you'd get ha'penny now and again off some of the customers you 
know. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
When there was someone in the district who people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember anything called rough music? If a chap was a wife beater or something like
 that the neighbours would stand outside and hammer tins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, you - you probably get a bit of jeering, one man lived near us - he used to beta his wife about but - you'd probably stand there jeering and hooting you know. That's about as far as you'd get because - you was really scared of him you know, he -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Who would be standing jeering, would this be kids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Mostly - juveniles you know, not - not many grown ups interfered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You don't remember anyone actually being forced to move out through this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No. No, I don't think so. The only way you moved out then was if you owed rent. Dodge out in the middle of the night which was - quite common with some people. You could in them days, you could move away and go and move into a
nother house. And they used to call it the moonlight felt. Yes. And that really did happen you know. Family'd be there, overnight - they'd be gone in the morning you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were you given lessons at all before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, not as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Pretty young as far as I remember. I - I won't say I was under four but it was round about that mark you know, you went to school earlier because - mother was at work you know and
 - they seemed to lean towards you to get you into the school. The five year old wasn't a strict rule them days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When you first started off did you go all day or just a half a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, all day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember what the hours were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, ordinary school hours as far as I remember. Nine 'til twelve. Two hours dinner. Two to half past three when we first started.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What kind of school was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Just a L.C.C. Board school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this mixed girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes,
 mixed, yes. Not classes. Girls and boys, we had two different sections you know, we was mixed classes up 'til - seven or eight and then we were separated, boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 On two sides of the building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Walk, you know it wasn't far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Five minutes, seven minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, used to go with me - oldest sisters you know. Pick up a couple of mates, like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, I think - as I remember I enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Very good, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No I don't think so. Really - behaviour, good manners - keep clean. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about ways of speaking or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think they - paid any special attention to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 They'd check you about your clothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, clothing and that, yes, and we
 used to have the - inspections once a month in your head and that you know. Nurses come round and send some home or - send some to the cleaning station you know. There was always somebody - dirty in the head and that you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well you'd have - lines you know, a punishment, stay in a quarter of an hour, and as you got older if it was too severe you got the cane, your name went in he book. Sent for the cane and book as they call
ed it in them days. Which really used to frighten you more than anything, if they sent you for the cane and book - you often went out and couldn't find it but - they found it for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did they use the cane very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I should say a lot more than
 they do nowadays, yes. I wouldn't say they was cruel, you know, I mean - I wouldn't say there was any heavy punishments you know, but - that cane and book was a tonic for you, no doubt about it, yes. I should think it was more the degrade - degrading par
t
 of it than the punishment you know, you had to go and get it yourself which meant going round to each class to find where it was you see. You had to go in that class and ask the teacher if the cane and book was in the room you see. I think that was worse
 than the punishment you know, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did the cane the girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What sort of offences would bring the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well, talking. Talking in class. Writing, you know, when you shouldn't be. Or - minor offences what 
wasn't caned was coming late or - fidgeting. Trivial things, you know what I mean. Yes, I think the children them days - was - you know, well I was going to say better behaved than they are now you know, I mean - it was quite a shock if anybody answered t
he teacher back or anything like that. Nowadays - seems to be a common }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 occurrence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
, you know what I mean. Yes. I don't think we were scared of the teachers or - it was more respect you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You had more respect for adults in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, you very seldom answered the teachers back. I mean if you - you overdone it, some of the boys, you were sent to the headmaster's room you know. Perhaps you'd get four or six handers as we used to call 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother show any interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, as far as she could, you know, under the circumstances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know if she ever visited the school or met the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Very seldom. Wasn't done a lot them days. No, not like it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did they used to have these sort of open days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I can't remember 'em, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you stay at the same school all your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes. Yes. I left when I was thirteen and a half, well most of these interviews they go on now older don't they you know. Up to sixteen, seven
teen today you know, we was really only children when we left school them days. You - we - I went in for exams to leave school, not to stay on. What they called a labour exam in them days, if you passed through it you was allowed to leave early, go out to
 work you see, so it was like the opposite system to what is now, now you sit to stop in but we used to call it the labour exam. I think I left when I was about thirteen and five months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You had to reach a certain standard in order to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That
's right, yes, yes. And your circumstances, you had - mostly widow, you know, children was allowed to go in for it, it wasn't a general rule. Yes. Yes. Yes. Anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did the other children come from similar type homes to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Practically, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, not as far as I remember. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 
'Cos they had their work cut out with big classes, I daresay, as far as I remember the average was perhaps forty a class, so - they didn't have a lot of time for - pay special attention.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Or any children who were left out of things for any reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember - a lot of it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
I don't think so, not in them days, no, I don't think it gained you anywhere you know. Now it does, if you pass your A's or your O's whatever it is, well of course they wasn't known in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you attend any part time education after you left school, any evening classes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so. No, I think I got as good as I was allowed to get, in the circumstances and the district where I lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you think it benefited you to attend school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Oh yes, I think so, yes. Specially - me home life, me mother out a lot, you know - you learnt extra care and respect and also you was out the way nearly all day, you wasn't running the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When you were at school you had this part time job from about the age of eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, twelve, of a morning, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have any other means or earning money while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this the only job you did while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That's the only job I can remember doing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You kept this up until you left school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, oh yes, a regular job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this with the same people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. Dairy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you know how you got this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well, through a neighbour I - a man - who run the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 milk round}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  lived two doors away from me. He took me on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What exactly did you have to do with this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh, just knock on the doors, ge
t the jugs and give out tin cans with the milk in, there was no bottles them days. We used to go out as far as I remember about six to eight, something like that, every morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How about Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, Saturdays and Sundays you - you worked longer. Helped wash up and that, same job. Was busier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So you worked quite a few hours on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. Seven day a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You worked about two hours in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Two hours of a morning and perhaps four, five h
ours Saturday and Sunday. Clearing up the yard, washing up, odd jobs you know. As far as I remember there was no restrictions then, on - labour, you know what I mean, I can't remember getting permission or anything like that to do it you know. 'Cos nowada
ys I think there are some restrictions, certain age, certain hours you know, but as far - I can never remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You must have worked on this job for about two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Two - two and a half - two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you get any paid holidays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I can't remember. Few - three, four bob. Something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You'd give this money to your mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And she'd give you a couple of coppers back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 She'd give you - yes, give you a tanner back or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What was the money you gave to your mum spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well - better clothing you know, used to have new shoes instead of secondhand ones. Something like that. Probably -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So it went mainly on clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
That's right. Probably little extra food, going out early, I'd have a breakfast you know, extra bit - breakfast. Extra oats or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 At the time did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, I suppose so. We was glad to hav
e it and - you was lucky if you got a job because - there was plenty - children in the neighbourhood who wanted them jobs, you know. And it is only the fact that he was a neighbour that I suppose I got my - so easy you know, what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So you felt quite lucky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Glad to get it, that's right, yes. They was always after them jobs you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 All right, yes, we didn't have a lot to do with the governor because - you worked for the man under him you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 The - the roundsman as you might say, he was your boss, he paid you, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did he pay you out of his wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 That's right, yes, yes, the more you done for him the - he paid you, you see, it wasn't anything to do with the governor you see.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this just to enable them to get finished quicker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Get finished quicker or spend an extra half hour in the pub, which he - he - he often done you know, used to sit outside in the float, it was horse and cart them days. That was
 his hobby you know, he'd probably finish early, specially Saturday or Sunday and - he'd - have extra half hour in the pub you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you feel about the work itself, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, I - as far as I can remember. Yes, I enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember whether going out to work altered your attitude to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so, no. I - can't remember much difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Job? Well I went as a - learning to be a clicker in the shoe trade straight away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You were in the shoe trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. That was me first job, yes. Thirteen and a half, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Whereabouts was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Hackney. What we call Mare Street, Hackney. About twenty minutes walk from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
As far as I can remember me mother took me, I don't know whether they advertised in the paper them days or - but she took - she come with me and got me the job. We had to take a character from the school. Got a - character, you took that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this considered quite a good job in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, a fair job. Yes, oh yes, you was learning a trade. That was - the main thing
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What exactly did you have to do when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 First started I used to sweep up. Light the fires. Go and get errands. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 
Men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  lunches, you know. We used to have a long stick with beer cans on it. Perhaps you'd get twenty teas, two cocoa. And you would pick up a couple of coppers that way. One }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  give you a ha'penny - penny on a Friday
 you know. And we used to get - toast for 'em, such things. 'Cos there were no canteens in the factory then. You practically all went out and got their lunches you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So you'd be a teaboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, really a teaboy, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Until another boy started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That's right, yes. Then you got promoted. You was learning cutting in between you know, you wasn't running errands all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You used to watch the other chaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That's right, yes. You started slowly cutting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this hand cutting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Hand - oh yes, hand cutting, no machines then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What hours did you work on this job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
As far as I remember eight 'til seven. And - about half past twelve, one o'clock Saturdays. About - fifty-two and a half hour I think it was the regulation in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you have holidays with pay on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Not pay, had holidays. Not paid. Make do, yes. Yes. In fact I've known children - other children that - that had to go and get another job because they - you know, couldn't afford to h
ave a week or two weeks without pay. Their parents made 'em go and get another job if possible. Specially with the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did the firm used to actually close down for a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. You had to have it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember what you were paid on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
What I was paid? I believe I started at fourteen shillings. As far as I can recollect. I seem to have it in me head it was seven but I couldn't guarantee, I - it'd be more or less what was paid at that time you know. I believe it was fourteen
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember whether you thought this was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, I suppose so, 'cos I was still very young wasn't I. It was really up to me mother more or less to know - if I was getting me - fair wage or - or not, you know, I mean at thirteen and a half you're still a boy ain't you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you give any of this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Oh yes, I used to get a shilling back when I first started there. Always come - walked home to dinner. Hackney which - we - we reckoned twenty minutes walk, twenty minutes dinner and twenty minutes back. That was the programme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You just had an hour for dinner did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, hour for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did your employer treat you on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh quite decent, they was rather a good class firm, first started at, yes - they was quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 fair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
, quite decent, as far as it was then possible, and clean firm. I mean, there was some - dirty firms and rough firms. They was pretty well known in the shoe trade, this firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How many people worked there, was it a big place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Fairly for them days I suppose. Three - four hundred I suppose. It was quite decent in them days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How did you get on there with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Pretty good, as far as I can remember, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 This would have been 1915 or '16?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. During the war, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How long did you stay on at this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What at that firm or the trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 As a trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 As a trade, oh - practically - all me life you know, had one or two breaks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So you started as a clicker at about thirteen and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And you stayed at this for about fourteen years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Until you needed an open air job for your health?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Health, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And you went on a bakers round for about twelve years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Twelve years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And then you opened your own general provisions shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Business, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And you say that was for about three years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes - two and a half to three years there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 Then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  you had a long spell of unemployment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. In the bad days, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 A year or eighteen months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes. In fact it was so long that - you know, as the time went on you didn't want to go to work. However good you was you know you lost the initiative, you got down and down, didn't matter whether you worked or not you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You really felt this in yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, oh yes, got you down you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You don't bother to get up and look for work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Oh you didn't look for work, no. Aft
er a time - the first few months how tried and then it's so hopeless and - you got mixed up with the regulars - you know - you get - sunk to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 their level}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  I suppose. I mean some of 'em thought you was mad looking for a job you know. We used to go to a traini
ng school afternoons, that was compulsory. Yes, and I - in fact I learnt boot - boot repairing there. That's different to clicking. But you met very low types there, no doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And you went back to the shoe trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 About 1934 to 1935?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 And you worked in the shoe trade ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Right up - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What were you when you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well I was foreman clicker then. Still clicking, yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What year did you retire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 '35. '65. '65, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Have you ever done any part time jobs or anything besides these jobs, other employment at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 What, since I've retired or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 While you were working?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I can't remember that. Well I say - in London I was a bookmaker for a couple of
 years, when the dogs started, yes, done quite well at that. In fact that's where I got most of me money to go into business. That was a sideline you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was this while you were on the bakers round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You'd pick up the slips on your round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, I used to go dogs. Bookmaker standing at the dogs. Business there, yes, me and a friend started up there. We done that for a couple of years. Yes, I was on the bakers round then. 'Cos when I was on the baker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 s round I dropped a
bout - thirty bob, two pound in money. In wages you know. To the shoe trade, yes. I think I was getting the average about four pound in the shoe trade and - the bakers was about two pounds seven and six, something like that. But no doubt it done me good. 
I was in a low state. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 
I thought it was very degrading coming from a - clicking job to a baker's roundsman, in fact I was quite ashamed too when I pulled this barrow along, the first couple of weeks you know but I - I - afterwards as the time went and I took
 it as a matter of course. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 In fact I enjoyed it, you know, open air life, meeting people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Would you have preferred any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 other type}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  of occupation to those you've done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so. I mean - fifty odd years of learning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 ,}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  about two years roughing it, it wasn't too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you serve an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 How long was the training period for the clicking job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well, I should say four or five years, handcutting - you started on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Four or five years training seems to be a long time without an actual apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I - I suppose on the level with a - apprenticeship but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 when}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  we didn't go in for apprenticeship because them days apprenticeship you didn't get paid at all, and of course I had to earn - help at home
. And there wasn't - as far as I remember there wasn't any apprenticeships in the shoe trade. In fact I don't - I don't think there is now, not actually - engineering and suchlike but - I mean, even this big factory here you don't get apprenticed, no. You
 
do in the engineers or - you might do different courses of training but the actual men on the board don't - do no apprenticeship you see. And of course hand cutting then, it naturally took you longer you know, you couldn't just go and use a knife - and in
 a few months, you had to be trained how to hold it, how to sharpen it and that. In fact my biggest trouble was when I went back in the shoe trade was getting me knife in condition, you know, it's surprising how - you lose the touch of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 This was all for upper leathers was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, upper leather, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, later on in life I - joined the union, yes. I - I don't think it was compulsory, but - I think you done it more or less in case you was out of wo
rk or ill, you got a few shillings benefit you know, you kind of - insurance more than - trade union ideals I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 This would be after 1918 would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you take part in any of the union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, just a ordinary member.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, I think we - practically the same interest. I think you had to work harder them days you know for to keep your job sort of thing, because - you couldn't affor
d to be chucked out, you couldn't go next door and get another job you know. You studied your job, you - you worked more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between craftsmen and other workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Perhaps you did a little bit. I mean, even in my job, clicking, you'd go to work in a suit and - collar and tie, whereas you'd find people in the road in their corduroys, red handkerchief sort of business, you know, I think you was inclin
ed to think you was a little bit above 'em. I don't say you was but you probably got that idea you know, I - yes, yes, I mean, we would clean our shoes every day, little things like that - that you thought you was above them sort of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 This was noticeable in dress was it as much as anything else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, as much as anything I should think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so. I don't - changed a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 When you first started work you continued to live at home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did starting work change your relationship with your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Or your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I don't think so, we was pretty close family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You didn't feel you were a bit more independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, well you - you knocked off a little jobs you know, I mean, I used to clean me older brothers shoes for a penny or something like that, of course when you started work you knock
 that off don't you, as above - your dignity, you didn't do them sort of jobs, you got more on a level with 'em I suppose. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you spend your Sunday any differently after you started work? Did you still go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, I didn't go 
to Sunday school, no. I probably - bit more sport, as I say we joined this club you know and weekends you'd be playing football or over the club grounds, more recreation you know, out more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Could you tell me anything more about this club, can you reme
mber any particular things you used to do, could you go there in the evenings for billiards or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, billiards, snooker - every evening it was open and Saturdays and Sundays you was - what we called over the sports ground you know.
 And I think we had to pay a penny a week subs, for the upkeep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you use this place very much in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, yes. Specially early days you know, when you first joined from say fourteen to sixteen you - you practically lived there you k
now. You could get a bun and a cup of tea - penny or something like that, and they had library, chess, draughts, you know, everything, there's no doubt about that, yes. And they'd have - little debating classes. Yes, different sections you know. And gymna
s
ium, boxing. That was our life really for Hackney Wick, it was well known and well noted. There'd be three or four hundred children there you know, an - and I daresay average them days there'd be hundred there every night. Yes. It was - well used, you kno
w, and you - you met better class boys, such as draughts, chess - in the library reading, you know, studying, a - a little higher class than our bringing up, you know what I mean. And - I think it helped to fetch you along you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You feel as though it had an influence on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Yes, I think so, mixing with 'em and that you know, you try to get to 'em, you - you go a little bit cleaner, a little bit smarter and - perhaps join in a debate and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you feel this was as an important effect on you as school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
I should say more. Yes, because you was older and - learning and - learning more about the world. Yes, definitely, I think - the club was a big asset in our lives no doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you take an interest in politics at all when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
No, not as far as I remember, I was - I was always Labour, but - I never went in for it serious, I used to enjoy the elections and - perhaps stop up half the night listening for the results, you know, I went as far as tha
t, but - I never took any part activity in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Do you remember why you were Labour and what person inclined you to the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Well I should think the conditions we lived in, you know, poor conditions. And we thought naturally Labour would
 do more for us. Also a little bit of tie up with the trade unionism helped. I mean, there - in our neighbourhood you daren't be - put a Conservative notice up in your window or anything. It was almost unheard of. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 In fact Hackney and Bow which was highly tied was the first Labour Borough you know to get M.P.'s in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Lansbury and Morrison was our figureheads in them days you know. So we was really in a - the first Labour strongholds actually. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 
Very, very few - we - as they say, you used to go up the better turnings where the teachers lived, then you start seeing the blue cardboards in the window - in our neighbourhood you was Conservative you kept - hid it under your hat.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 People sometimes say that in those days there was pressure from employers or people like this to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Vote, no, I can't remember it. No. No. Even in the club - it wasn't allowed, as I daresay all them guv'nors was - Tories you know, different class, but I mean it was - barred - you - you weren't allowed to talk politics.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you take part in political activity other than election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Your leisure time changed quite a lot between when you left school and when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Were there any other changes in your life? Were there other sorts of things that you started doing in your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 I might have gone to the - pictures a bit more often. Mixed with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15077704\charrsid15482426 
girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426  a bit more I suppose of an evening. No, I wouldn't say it made a big difference, you got smarter, you bought - you know, helped buy your own clothes gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Where would you go in the evening if you didn't go to the club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Perhaps pictures once a week but - as I say, we was lucky, it was nearly all club. Nearly all club life, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you make any new friends at this time or did they mainly carry on from your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Well - early days you would carry on with your schooldays and then as I say you began to mix with - better class boys to me you know. And the club encouraged it you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, not a lot, there wasn't the room - really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you make any special friends, any boys or girls at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 No, generally mixed, you know. Few of us used to go about together. 'Cos there's no girls all
owed in the club, in them days. So that restricted you a lot, you used to - talk to them outside. Lark about with 'em you know outside the club but - it wasn't encouraged, it was - purely simply a boys club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Where would you pick up girls in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Oh you'd just walk - I mean perhaps a weekend you'd walk up what we called Mare Street, that was the main road and - you'd just walk up and down and have a chat with girls and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So it would be on the street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 On the street, yes, defi
nitely, yes. No, I think - not much coffee bar. In fact you'd go to the pictures once a week with a girl friend or Hackney Empire you know. But - you done most of it in the streets, no doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Was Hackney Empire a music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, music hall Monday night, music hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 You could afford to go to this when you had a bit more cash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did your mother expect to meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 As they got older, yes, I should say she did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did you still have to be home by a certain time after you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes, up to - what - probably seventeen around about ten o'clock was - was our time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did she expect to know where you were going before you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 As a rule, yes. As much as I c
an tell you 'cos I was getting on then when she started this business, and - she gradually started, she used to go round and - help the doctor or the nurse, fetch the baby in, wash the baby. She'd probably do ten days or two weeks there and if I remember 
r
ight she got somewhere about twenty-five or thirty shillings a week for then. And it quite spread with the Jewish families and she got quite a regular booking. Because - and also if you have a boy when they're circumcised they used to put a bowl on the ta
ble and the perks used to go in for the nurse. And they had to put silver in, yes, and all the guests at this - circumcise - so it was really quite a decent business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 That could be quite profitable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes, and of course - it also gave her free
dom on the house, she wasn't - tied down to any regular house you know. 'Cos I can remember her when I was young, people knocking on the door in the middle of the night - take her out to see to these cases you know. It - it was a kind of a - unregistered 
nurse really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Did she used to do some of this while she was still at the shirt factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
Oh no, no, this was later when she was at home. We was at work, well I was, I was the only one, the others was married then, I was - the last one at home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 About how old do you think you were when she gave up the factory?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 
I think she gave up near enough when I went out to work, or soon after. You know, she had coming - sister coming in you see, all handed in together you know and then she sta
rted this business and I - I should think she earned more at this than she did at the - shirt factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9006662 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 So she probably started this about 1916 or '17?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12478316 JP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Yes. Yes. And of course it didn't tie her down so much as the factory you see, she'd probably 
go out a couple of hours in the morning, couple of hours in the evening, settle the mother down, bath the baby, such things like that you know. And it's surprising the - the work she got. They was - really good class }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4022478\charrsid15482426 of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166979\charrsid15482426 Jews you know. Actually it was quite a good lift up for her as regards finance, way of living you know.
